---
const uid = Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8);
---

<figure class="mx-auto max-w-2xl my-10">
  <svg
    width="680"
    height="520"
    viewBox="0 0 680 520"
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
    class="w-full h-auto"
    role="img"
    aria-labelledby={`endowment-stack-title-${uid}`}
    aria-describedby={`endowment-stack-desc-${uid}`}
    style="font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"
  >
    <title id={`endowment-stack-title-${uid}`}>South Africa's endowment stack</title>
    <desc id={`endowment-stack-desc-${uid}`}>
      A six-tier inventory of South Africa's strategic endowments. Demographic window: a young
      population with a demographic dividend open for roughly fifteen to twenty years. Mineral
      endowment: world-leading reserves of platinum-group metals, manganese, chromium, and vanadium.
      Financial depth: the deepest capital markets and most sophisticated financial and legal
      services sector in Africa. Geographic position: a two-ocean coast astride the Cape route,
      making the country the natural logistics gateway to SADC. Industrial and logistics base:
      residual but decayed rail, ports, and manufacturing — a reconstructible foundation. Diplomatic
      capital: non-aligned middle-power credibility and BRICS membership, a declining but genuine
      asset. Unlike the doctrinal stack, the endowment stack is a parallel portfolio of assets
      rather than a hierarchy.
    </desc>

    <!-- Figure heading -->
    <text x="340" y="24" text-anchor="middle" font-size="13" font-weight="600" fill="#7A5C1F" letter-spacing="1.2">
      SOUTH AFRICA&apos;S ENDOWMENT STACK
    </text>
    <text x="340" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#4A4A4A" font-style="italic">
      Six strategic assets in the country&rsquo;s hand — a portfolio, not a hierarchy
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 1: Demographic Window -->
    <rect x="70" y="78" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#5E4613"/>
    <text x="92" y="100" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#E8D9A8" letter-spacing="1.4">
      I &middot; DEMOGRAPHIC WINDOW
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="120" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#FFFFFF">
      Young population &middot; demographic dividend
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="120" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#E8D9A8" font-style="italic">
      15&ndash;20 years
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 2: Mineral Endowment -->
    <rect x="70" y="140" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#7A5C1F"/>
    <text x="92" y="162" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#F0E6C8" letter-spacing="1.4">
      II &middot; MINERAL ENDOWMENT
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="182" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#FFFFFF">
      PGMs &middot; manganese &middot; chromium &middot; vanadium
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="182" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#F0E6C8" font-style="italic">
      World-leading
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 3: Financial Depth -->
    <rect x="70" y="202" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#A68A2B"/>
    <text x="92" y="224" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#F7EFD4" letter-spacing="1.4">
      III &middot; FINANCIAL DEPTH
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="244" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#FFFFFF">
      Capital markets &middot; legal &amp; financial services
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="244" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#F7EFD4" font-style="italic">
      Africa-leading
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 4: Geographic Position -->
    <rect x="70" y="264" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#BFA455"/>
    <text x="92" y="286" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#3A2E0C" letter-spacing="1.4">
      IV &middot; GEOGRAPHIC POSITION
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="306" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#1A1A1A">
      Two-ocean coast &middot; Cape route &middot; SADC gateway
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="306" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#3A2E0C" font-style="italic">
      Structural
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 5: Industrial & logistics base -->
    <rect x="70" y="326" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#D9C586"/>
    <text x="92" y="348" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#4A3A0F" letter-spacing="1.4">
      V &middot; INDUSTRIAL &amp; LOGISTICS BASE
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="368" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#1A1A1A">
      Rail &middot; ports &middot; residual manufacturing
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="368" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#4A3A0F" font-style="italic">
      Decayed &middot; reconstructible
    </text>

    <!-- Tier 6: Diplomatic capital -->
    <rect x="70" y="388" width="540" height="56" rx="6" fill="#F3EBDA"/>
    <text x="92" y="410" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#7A5C1F" letter-spacing="1.4">
      VI &middot; DIPLOMATIC CAPITAL
    </text>
    <text x="92" y="430" font-size="14" font-weight="500" fill="#1A1A1A">
      Non-aligned middle power &middot; BRICS member
    </text>
    <text x="588" y="430" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#7A5C1F" font-style="italic">
      Declining &middot; genuine
    </text>

    <!-- Portfolio bracket (right margin) -->
    <path d="M 628,88 Q 638,88 638,105 L 638,417 Q 638,434 628,434" stroke="#7A5C1F" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round"/>
    <text x="654" y="264" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7A5C1F" letter-spacing="0.5" transform="rotate(90 654 264)">
      PORTFOLIO
    </text>

    <!-- Caption -->
    <text x="340" y="484" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#5F5E5A">
      A parallel portfolio of strategic assets — no tier binds the others; each stands or falls on its own use.
    </text>
    <text x="340" y="502" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" fill="#5F5E5A" font-style="italic">
      The strategic question is whether the doctrinal stack above is aligned to the endowment stack below.
    </text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption class="sr-only">
    Figure: South Africa&rsquo;s endowment stack — six strategic assets (minerals, financial depth,
    geographic position, demographic window, industrial and logistics base, diplomatic capital)
    presented as a parallel portfolio rather than a doctrinal hierarchy.
  </figcaption>
</figure>
